    <p> Here in Sydney there are at least one fireworks on weekends. Mostly even several. Often distributed across the city at the same time. One of them is in Darling Harbor every Saturday at 9 p.m., which is only 15 minutes walk from the apartment. On Saturday November 24th I was on the way to the fireworks again to practice a little for the Silverster photos. When I arrived there were a lot of people on site, and it was still a few hours to the fireworks. </p>
    <p> When a choir suddenly started singing Christmas carols behind me. Here in Sydney, the large Christmas tree is ceremoniously brought to illuminating. I promptly looked for a good place to see the show. Over time, of course, it got fuller and full. Definitely not for my dad. Around 8 p.m. the whole show finally started with a water skiing Santa. </p>
    <p> Then a parade of Santa Clauses and women. The Christmas carols sung around the square. Then the Schow in the harbor basin really started. Several larger sailing messenger drove around. In between, several Santa Clauses in fast boats or in formation on water skis. </p>
