    <p> In between, pontoons with huge matrosmo kas and a Christmas present were as large as a small house. There were also two dragon boats, fully occupied with Santa Clauses. I have to say that the whole thing takes place in a harbor basin, which is as big as the inlands in Hamburg, if not smaller. To make matters worse, the fireworks were quite in the center of the harbor basin around all of them. </p>
    <p> The real "head" Santa Claus for this day was driven to the event in a small boat of the Australian military. This then climbed to the pontoon with the gift and disappeared behind it. A few minutes later, he appeared over the water behind the pontoon and flew, with the help of a water-operated jet pack, once and then to press the place on a very specific point on a button and switch on the large Christmas tree. </p>
    <p> The whole thing was accompanied by a small but fine fireworks. Unfortunately, a huge air of Santa Claus was placed in front of the lens in the course of the evening, which wobbled through the picture all the time and tried to mess up one or the other. Which he sometimes managed. </p>
    <p> In between, everyone had to keep silent for 10 seconds so that a huge panorama can be taken. </p>
